In ''[[NetHack]]'', the letter '''A''' serves the following purposes:

* {{white|a}} represents an [[insect]]:
** {{monsymlink|giant ant}}
** {{monsymlink|killer bee}}
** {{monsymlink|soldier ant}}
** {{monsymlink|fire ant}}
** {{monsymlink|giant beetle}}
** {{monsymlink|queen bee}}

* {{white|A}} represents an [[angelic being]]:
** {{monsymlink|couatl}}
** {{monsymlink|Aleax}}
** {{monsymlink|Angel}}
** {{monsymlink|ki-rin}}
** {{monsymlink|Archon}}

* It is also used for the following [[keyboard]] controls:
** Press {{kbd|A}} to use or [[apply]] an item.
** Press {{kbd|shift|A}} to [[take off]] multiple items at once.
** Press {{kbd|ctrl|A}} to redo the previous command entered.

==Historical uses==
In hack121 and PDP-11 Hack, variants of [[Jay Fenlason's Hack]], [[acid blob]]s and giant ants used the {{white|a}} and {{white|A}} glyphs respectively, and continued to from [[Hack 1.0]] to [[NetHack 2.3e]].

In [[NetHack 3.0.0]], acid blobs are moved to the [[blob]] [[monster class]] at {{white|b}}, and giant ants are moved to {{white|a}} with other [[insect]]s including the [[giant beetle]] (formerly {{white|b}} prior to 3.0.0) - {{white|A}} is used for the [[apelike creature]]s, which consists of the [[ape]] and [[carnivorous ape]] in this version. [[NetHack 3.1.0]] introduces the angelic being monster class and gives them the {{white|A}} glyph, moving apelike creatures to {{white|Y}}; the [[yeti]] is merged into the apelike creature monster class, which uses its former monster class macro.

